'''911陰謀論'''（英文：''9/11 Conspiracy Theories''）是一種政治觀點，認為2001年9月11日發生的美國[[九一一事件|九一一事件]]是一場政治[[陰謀|陰謀]]。該論點認為，官方對9/11恐怖襲擊事件的描述中具有多個疑點，例如飛機不可能撞毀一摩天大廈，[[五角大樓|五角大樓]]的缺口直徑與飛機直徑不符，[[聯合航空93號班機|聯合航空93號班機]]的碎片散佈區域以及劫機者的生死等。襲擊後，美國政府立即公佈劫機者名單，不久後以消滅[[塔利班|塔利班]]政權及捕捉[[賓·拉登|賓·拉登]]為名向[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]宣戰，之後又以搜尋[[大殺傷力武器|大殺傷力武器]]為名向[[伊拉克|伊拉克]]宣戰；因此陰謀論者認為該襲擊目的是[[喬治·W·布希|喬治·W·布希]]政府自導自演，為鞏固其統治合法性<ref>參見[[2000年美國總統選舉|2000年美國總統選舉]]。</ref>，转移媒体焦点，維護美国的國際地位，達到霸權和平目的，以便控制世界。政府和獨立機構的調查均否認陰謀的存在<ref>{{Cite web|title=9/11 Conspiracy Theories - Debunking the Myths - World Trade Center - Pentagon - Flight 93 - Popular Mechanics|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101024055909/http://www.popularmechanics.com/911-myths?click=main_sr|accessdate=2019-11-04|date=2010-10-24|work=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Purdue study supports WTC collapse findings - USATODAY.com|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131223024435/https://usatoday30.usatoday.com/tech/news/2007-06-20-fireproofing-wtc-collapse_N.htm|accessdate=2019-11-04|date=2013-12-23|work=web.archive.org}}</ref>，但陰謀論支持者仍認為官方敘述存在被忽視的疑點。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Click Here for Conspiracy|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2006/08/loosechange200608|accessdate=2019-11-04|last=Nast|first=Condé|work=Vanity Fair|language=en|archive-date=2015-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150112235921/http://www.vanityfair.com/ontheweb/features/2006/08/loosechange200608|dead-url=no}}</ref>

一些阴谋论反对者对陰謀論的一些观点进行了反驳。同时九一一陰謀論不乏知名人士相信，更有組織地遊行示威、出版書籍、纪录片等向民眾宣傳九一一陰謀論，其中較著名的便是纪录片《[[脆弱的變化|脆弱的變化]]》。2013年4月2日，根據一家專門分析政治動向的美國機構 — [[公共政策民調基金會|公共政策民調基金會]]所做的調查顯示，有11%的美國民眾投票認為，九一一襲擊是美國政府的自導自演<ref>{{cite web|language=en|url=http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2013/04/conspiracy-theory-poll-results-.html|title=Conspiracy Theory Poll Results|publisher=[[公共政策民調基金會|公共政策民調基金會]]|date=2013-04-02|accessdate=2017-04-03|archive-date=2017-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170930093655/http://www.publicpolicypolling.com/main/2013/04/conspiracy-theory-poll-results-.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

美國國家標準技術研究所（NIST）和科學研究雜誌《Popular Mechanics》均對陰謀論觀點進行了調查，認為陰謀論不成立。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=NIST and the World Trade Center|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090529010501/http://wtc.nist.gov/NCSTAR1/|accessdate=2019-11-04|date=2009-05-29|work=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Wayback Machine|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080928013317/http://wtc.nist.gov/media/NIST_NCSTAR_1A_for_public_comment.pdf|accessdate=2019-11-04|date=2008-09-28|work=web.archive.org}}</ref><ref name="popmech">{{Cite web|title=Afterword--Debunking 9/11 Myths - Popular Mechanics|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061024062122/http://www.popularmechanics.com/science/research/4199607.html|accessdate=2019-11-04|date=2006-10-24|work=web.archive.org}}</ref>《Popular Mechanics》主編更譴責陰謀論者借國難發財。<ref name=popmech />9/11調查委員會和大部分土木工程師均認同噴氣式飛機的高速撞擊摩擦及{{Link-en|航空燃油|Jet fuel}}所產生的大火（而非定向爆破）的確是導致大廈倒塌的原因<ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Bažant | first1 = Z. K. P. | authorlink1 = Zdenek Bažant | last2 = Verdure | first2 = M. | doi = 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9399(2007)133:3(308) | title = Mechanics of Progressive Collapse: Learning from World Trade Center and Building Demolitions | journal = Journal of Engineering Mechanics | volume = 133 | issue = 3 | pages = 308–319 | year = 2007 | url = http://www.civil.northwestern.edu/people/bazant/PDFs/Papers/466.pdf | publisher = [[American_Society_of_Civil_Engineers|American Society of Civil Engineers]] | quote = As generally accepted by the community of specialists in structural mechanics and structural engineering (though not by a few outsiders claiming a conspiracy with planted explosives), the failure scenario was as follows: [continues with a four-part scenario of progressive structural failure]. | access-date = 2019-11-04 | archive-date = 2007-08-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070809030224/http://www.civil.northwestern.edu/people/bazant/PDFs/Papers/466.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = Bažant | first1 = Z. K. P. | authorlink1 = Zdenek Bažant | last2 = Le | first2 = J. L. | last3 = Greening | first3 = F. R. | last4 = Benson | first4 = D. B. | title = What Did and Did Not Cause Collapse of World Trade Center Twin Towers in New York? | doi = 10.1061/(ASCE)0733-9399(2008)134:10(892) | journal = Journal of Engineering Mechanics | volume = 134 | issue = 10 | page = 892 | year = 2008 | url = http://www.civil.northwestern.edu/people/bazant/PDFs/Papers/00%20WTC%20Collapse%20-%20What%20Did%20%26%20Did%20Not%20Cause%20It.pdf | publisher = [[American_Society_of_Civil_Engineers|American Society of Civil Engineers]] | quote = Universally though has the foregoing explanation of collapse been accepted by the communities of structural engineers and structural mechanics researchers, some outside critics have nevertheless exploited various unexplained observations to disseminate allegations of controlled demolition. | access-date = 2019-11-04 | archive-date = 2015-09-23 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150923204407/http://www.civil.northwestern.edu/people/bazant/PDFs/Papers/00%20WTC%20Collapse%20-%20What%20Did%20%26%20Did%20Not%20Cause%20It.pdf | dead-url = no }}</ref>，但亦有組織不認同<ref>{{Cite web|title=U.S. skeptics to speak of 9-11 cover-up at three Canadian universities {{!}} The Star|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2010/04/30/us_skeptics_to_speak_of_911_coverup_at_three_canadian_universities.html|accessdate=2019-11-04|work=thestar.com|language=en|archive-date=2019-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191104141605/https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2010/04/30/us_skeptics_to_speak_of_911_coverup_at_three_canadian_universities.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

